   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1847_08_31_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="Id_where"/>Edgeworths town
                  <date when="1816-08-04">Aug<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> 31 47</date>
               </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>
               I forgive you - not<lb/>
               because you deserve it<lb/>
               But because I cannot<lb/>
               help it I am so <choice>
                  <orig>over<lb/>
               -joyed</orig>
                  <reg>overjoyed</reg>
               </choice> to hear of your<lb/>
               dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockC1">Charlottes</persName>
               <choice>
                  <orig>hap-<lb/>
               py</orig>
                  <reg>happy</reg>
               </choice> marriage and <choice>
                  <orig>sym<lb/>
               pathesise</orig>
                  <reg>sympathize</reg>
               </choice> with you so<lb/>
               heartily in your honest<lb/>
               parental delight,<lb/>
               handsome &amp; all! -<lb/>
               &amp; high born and a<lb/>
               fortune good enough<lb/>
               and two houses <unclear>hold</unclear>
               <lb/>
               the fashionable - Oh<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1847_08_31_page02.jpg"/>
               I am twice your friend<lb/>
               my dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">Mr. Lockhart</persName>
               <lb/>
               I always doubted<lb/>
               till now that <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SmitA1">Smith</persName>
               <lb/>
               was right in his theory<lb/>
               of Moral sentiments<lb/>
               when he says that<lb/>
               Mankind womankind<lb/>
               inclusive was ever most<lb/>
               prone to sympathise<lb/>
               with the rich and <choice>
                  <orig>pros-<lb/>
               perous</orig>
                  <reg>prosperous</reg>
               </choice> I used to<lb/>
               fancy that Sympathy<lb/>
               was for the unfortunate<lb/>
               <unclear>most</unclear> - "Pity dropping soft<lb/>
               The sadly pleasing tear"<lb/>
               But nous avons changée<lb/>
               tout cela - and I am<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1847_08_31_page03.jpg"/>
               now quite of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SmitA1">Adam Smiths</persName>
               <lb/>
               opinion -<lb/>
               I am not come<lb/>
               to thinking about the<lb/>
               new Life yet - But I am<lb/>
               glad I did not affront<lb/>
               you by my <choice>
                  <orig>presumpti<lb/>
               ous</orig>
                  <reg>presumptuous</reg>
               </choice> advising and I<lb/>
               shall do the same again<lb/>
               as soon as you go to work<lb/>
               again which I hope<lb/>
               will not be for a great<lb/>
               while yet - Very good<lb/>
               for your health this<lb/>
               Hang sorrow &amp; Cast away<lb/>
               care - Send the enclosed<lb/>
               Notes of congratulation to<lb/>
               my dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockC1">Charlotte</persName>
            </p>
            <closer>
               Hope &amp; believe<lb/>
               me Yours sincerely &amp; <choice>
                  <orig>affec<hi rend="superscript">ly</hi>
                  </orig>
                  <reg>affectionately</reg>
               </choice>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
